## Module folder pattern (repeat per domain)

```
modules/leads/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ index.ts              # export { default as leadsRouter } from './leads.routes'
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ leads.routes.ts       # Thin HTTP: parse req в†’ call service в†’ res.json
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ leads.service.ts      # Business logic + DB access
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ leads.validator.ts    # Zod schemas for body/query/params
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ leads.types.ts        # LeadDTO, ListLeadsQuery, вЂ¦
в””в”Ђв”Ђ leads.constants.ts    # Module-local defaults (optional)
```

## Layer responsibilities

| Layer | File | Responsibility |
|-------|------|----------------|
| Routes | `*.routes.ts` | HTTP only: validate input, call service, map status codes |
| Service | `*.service.ts` | Business rules, Drizzle queries, side effects (email, audit) |
| Validator | `*.validator.ts` | Zod вЂ” no DB, no req/res |
| Types | `*.types.ts` | Module DTOs; infer from Zod where possible |
| Middleware | `shared/middleware/` | Auth, global error handler вЂ” reusable |
| DB schema | `db/schema/` | Tables only вЂ” no HTTP logic |

## Route conventions

- All routes mounted under `/api` via `src/routes/index.ts`
- Path constants in `shared/url-helpers/route-paths.ts` вЂ” no magic strings in modules
- **Public:** `POST /api/leads`, `GET /api/projects`, `GET /api/content/*`
- **Protected (`requireAuth`):** all admin CRUD (GET/PATCH/DELETE on leads, projects, documents, services, content admin, audit)
- Auth module: `POST /api/auth/login`, `GET /api/auth/verify`, `POST /api/auth/logout`, `POST /api/auth/change-password`

## Shared lib rules

| Folder | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `shared/api-helpers/` | Response helpers, pagination, ID parsing |
| `shared/url-helpers/` | Route path constants |
| `shared/constants/` | Session TTL, default limits, app name |
| `shared/enums/` | LeadStatus, AuditAction, UserRole |
| `shared/types/` | Express augmentation, ApiError, PaginatedResult |
| `shared/lib/` | Cross-cutting infra (logger, S3, email) |

Promote code to `shared/` only when **2+ modules** need it.

## Security (required)

- bcrypt for passwords вЂ” never plaintext in `site_settings`
- DB-backed `sessions` table вЂ” not in-memory session flags
- httpOnly cookie `sessionId`; validate in `requireAuth` on every protected route
- CORS: explicit frontend origin(s), `credentials: true`
- Validate all inputs with module validators before service calls

## Migration from current layout

- Move `src/routes/*.ts` logic в†’ `src/modules/*/` (routes stay thin)
- Consolidate `src/workplace/db/` в†’ `src/db/` вЂ” delete workplace duplicates
- Replace `src/lib/objectStorage.ts` Replit GCS в†’ `shared/lib/object-storage.ts` (AWS S3)
- Remove `src/workplace/api-spec`, `api-client-react`, `api-zod` after validators live in modules

## Naming conventions

- Files: `kebab-case` or `domain.layer.ts` вЂ” `leads.service.ts`, `require-auth.ts`
- Services: exported functions вЂ” `createLead`, `listLeads`, `updateLead`
- Validators: `CreateLeadBody`, `ListLeadsQuery` (Zod exports)
- Routers: default export Express `Router` from `*.routes.ts`

## Do not

- Put DB queries or business logic directly in route handlers
- Import across modules' internals вЂ” use module `index.ts` or shared layer
- Reference Replit sidecar (`127.0.0.1:1106`) or `@google-cloud/storage`
- Leave admin endpoints unprotected
- Add new code under `src/workplace/`
